  "prompt": "What are the legal precedents related to money laundering cases?",
  "response": "There are various legal precedents related to money laundering cases. Some key examples include:\n\n1. United States v. BCCI (1991)\n- Major international bank convicted of widespread money laundering\n- Established significant legal standards for prosecuting financial institutions\n\n2. Bank of Credit and Commerce International (BCCI) case\n- Landmark case demonstrating complex international money laundering schemes\n- Highlighted regulatory gaps in financial oversight\n\n3. United States v. Carpenter (1987)\n- Supreme Court ruling on insider trading and financial fraud\n- Helped define legal boundaries of financial crimes\n\n4. Proceeds of Crime Act (UK, 2002)\n- Comprehensive legal framework for money laundering prosecution\n- Established broader definitions of money laundering offenses\n\n5. Basel Committee recommendations\n- International standards for anti-money laundering practices\n- Influential in developing global legal approaches\n\nThese precedents have shaped modern anti-money laundering legal standards. However, specific details can vary by jurisdiction. Legal professionals would have the most comprehensive and current understanding of these cases.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these precedents?",
